quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  19,59,But they were succeeded by generations who neglected prayer and followed their lusts and so will soon face the evil consequences
  19,60,"As for those who repent, believe, and do good, it is they who will be admitted into Paradise, never being denied any reward"
  19,61,"˹They will be in˺ the Gardens of Eternity, promised in trust by the Most Compassionate to His servants. Surely His promise will be fulfilled"
  19,62,There they will never hear any idle talk—only ˹greetings of˺ peace. And there they will have their provisions morning and evening
  19,63,"That is Paradise, which We will grant to whoever is devout among Our servants"
  19,64,"“We only descend by the command of your Lord. To Him belongs whatever is before us, and whatever is behind us, and everything in between. And your Lord is never forgetful"
  19,65,"˹He is the˺ Lord of the heavens, and the earth, and everything in between. So worship Him ˹alone˺, and be steadfast in His worship. Do you know of anyone equal to Him ˹in His attributes˺?”"
  19,66,"Yet ˹some˺ people ask ˹mockingly˺, “After I die, will I really be raised to life again?”"
  19,67,"Do ˹such˺ people not remember that We created them before, when they were nothing"
  19,68,"By your Lord ˹O Prophet˺! We will surely gather them along with the devils, and then set them around Hell on their knees"
  19,69,Then We will certainly begin by dragging out of every group the ones most defiant to the Most Compassionate
  19,70,And We truly know best who is most deserving of burning in it
  19,71,There is none of you who will not pass over it. ˹This is˺ a decree your Lord must fulfil
  19,72,"Then We will deliver those who were devout, leaving the wrongdoers there on their knees"
  19,73,"When Our clear revelations are recited to them, the disbelievers ask the believers ˹mockingly˺, “Which of the two of us is better in status and superior in assembly?”"
  19,74,"˹Imagine, O Prophet˺ how many peoples We have destroyed before them, who were far better in luxury and splendour"
  19,75,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “Whoever is ˹entrenched˺ in misguidance, the Most Compassionate will allow them plenty of time, until—behold!—they face what they are threatened with: either the torment or the Hour. Only then will they realize who is worse in position and inferior in manpower.”"
  19,76,And Allah increases in guidance those who are ˹rightly˺ guided. And the everlasting good deeds are far better with your Lord in reward and in outcome
  19,77,"Have you seen ˹O Prophet˺ the one who rejects Our revelations yet boasts, “I will definitely be granted ˹plenty of˺ wealth and children ˹if there is an afterlife˺.”"
  19,78,Has he looked into the unseen or taken a pledge from the Most Compassionate
  19,79,Not at all! We certainly record whatever he claims and will increase his punishment extensively
  19,80,"And We will inherit what he boasts of, and he will come before Us all by himself"
  19,81,"They have taken other gods, instead of Allah, seeking strength ˹and protection˺ through them"
  19,82,But no! Those ˹gods˺ will deny their worship and turn against them
  19,83,"Do you ˹O Prophet˺ not see that We have sent the devils against the disbelievers, constantly inciting them"
  19,84,"So do not be in haste against them, for indeed We are ˹closely˺ counting down their days"
  19,85,˹Watch for˺ the Day We will gather the righteous before the Most Compassionate as an honoured delegation
  19,86,and drive the wicked to Hell like a thirsty herd
  19,87,"None will have the right to intercede, except those who have taken a covenant from the Most Compassionate"
  19,88,"They say, “The Most Compassionate has offspring.”"
  19,89,You have certainly made an outrageous claim
  19,90,"by which the heavens are about to burst, the earth to split apart, and the mountains to crumble to pieces"
  19,91,in protest of attributing children to the Most Compassionate
  19,92,It does not befit ˹the majesty of˺ the Most Compassionate to have children
  19,93,There is none in the heavens or the earth who will not return to the Most Compassionate in full submission
  19,94,"Indeed, He fully knows them and has counted them precisely"
  19,95,And each of them will return to Him on the Day of Judgment all alone
  19,96,"As for those who believe and do good, the Most Compassionate will ˹certainly˺ bless them with ˹genuine˺ love"
  19,97,"Indeed, We have made this ˹Quran˺ easy in your own language ˹O Prophet˺ so with it you may give good news to the righteous and warn those who are contentious"
  19,98,"˹Imagine˺ how many peoples We have destroyed before them! Do you ˹still˺ see any of them, or ˹even˺ hear from them the slightest sound"